🍂 Rejoignez-nous à notre pique-nique de rentrée!🍂 

🍂 Join Us for the French Course Union’s Welcome Picnic! 🍂

📅 Mercredi, le 25 septembre 
⏰ 12h00 à 14h00
📍 Queen’s Park, rue St Joseph et Queens Park Cres. E

📣 
Rencontrez de nouveaux et anciens amis tout en profitant d’une pizza lors de notre premier événement de l’année ! Que vous soyez en votre première ou dernière année, ou simplement curieux à propos du département de français, tout le monde est le bienvenu ! Ne manquez pas un après-midi parfait de plaisir, de nourriture et de français ! Aucun souci si vous ne pouvez pas rester la durée de l’événement, passez nous dire bonjour quand même ! Venez en grand nombre ! 😊

Veuillez remplir le formulaire dans notre bio si vous envisagez de venir, afin de nous donner une idée du nombre de participants à prévoir !
On a hâte de vous rencontrer ! 🍕🎉 

📣 
Come and meet new and old friends while enjoying some pizza at our first event of the year! Whether you’re in your first or last year, or just curious about the French department, everyone is welcome! Don’t miss out on a perfect afternoon of fun, food, and French! No worries if you can’t stay for the whole thing, come by and say hi anyway! 😊

Please fill out the form in our bio if you’re considering attending so that we have an idea of how many people to expect!
Can’t wait to see you there! 🍕🎉

Hey folders,

Let’s take some time this week to appreciate the beautiful land that our university takes place on~ while Toronto is super urban, the rest of Canada is filled with scenic landscapes and nature!! We can take some time to focus on the natural beauties of this land in our Nature of the North workshop this week :D

✧ ˖°⛰️ ༄ ✧ ˖°⛰️ ༄

This week’s workshop will take place 📆 Friday, September 27th, from 🕔  5:00 - 7:00 PM in 📍 RW143 (sorry for changing the time and room again ☹️). If you guys need help getting to the workshop room, it should be across from the room from last week. Diagrams and origami paper will be provided as usual!

The featured models this week are:
🍁  Maple leaf (Satoshi Kamiya)
🪿  Canada goose (Roman Diaz)
🌰  Acorn
🍄  Mushroom (Joost Langeveld)

If you’re interested in joining us, please let us know on our Discord to help us gauge this weeks attendance :))

Thanks once again to our art director Daniel for this beautiful banner!!

✧ ˖°⛰️ ༄ ✧ ˖°⛰️ ༄

See you guys on Friday!!
